==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''[[rīchi]]'', akin to Old Saxon ''rīki'', both from a Celtic language, compare Irish [[rí]]
===Adjective===
'''reich'''

# [[rich]]
#:''Sie ist sehr '''reich'''.'' - She's very rich.
#:''Es ist '''reich''' an Ballaststoffen.'' - It's rich in fiber.

